. CHAP. LXII. The disposition of the tribes in Galilee.

THE country of Samaria contained only two tribes, and those of the brethren‚ Ephraim and Manasses: Galilee four, Issachar‚ Zebulun, Nephthalim, and Asher, and a part also of the Danites.

The maps agree indeed about the order in which these tribes were seated, but about the proper place of their situa- tion, Oh how great a disagreement is there among them! The tribe of Issachar held the south country of Galilee : some maps place it on the south of the sea of Gennesaoet, not illy: but it is ill done of them to stretch it unto the sea itzelf : and others, worst of all, who set it on the west of that sea.
